<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,546,859]" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">
Among phallodrilines, only a few 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Knollner" authorityYear="1935" box="[547,662,546,571]" class="Clitellata" family="Naididae" genus="Aktedrilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[547,662,546,571]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">Aktedrilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species, with or without spermathecae, transfer sperm by attaching spermatophores to the partner's body wall. These species were initially classified in the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Hrabe, 1973" authorityName="Hrabe" authorityYear="1973" class="Clitellata" family="Naididae" genus="Bacescuella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1217,1352,582,607]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">Bacescuella</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation pageId="9" pageNumber="50" refId="ref11440" refString="Hrabe, S. (1973) A contribution to the knowledge of marine Oligochaeta, mainly from the Black Sea. T ravaux du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle &quot; Grigore Antipa &quot;, 13, 27 - 38." type="journal article">Hrabě, 1973</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but that genus was placed in synonymy with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Knollner" authorityYear="1935" box="[731,846,618,643]" class="Clitellata" family="Naididae" genus="Aktedrilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[731,846,618,643]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">Aktedrilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Erséus (1987). At present, six 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Knollner" authorityYear="1935" box="[1232,1347,618,643]" class="Clitellata" family="Naididae" genus="Aktedrilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1232,1347,618,643]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">Aktedrilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species produce spermatophores; these are dome-shaped, on short stalks or directly attached to the body wall (
<figureCitation box="[1331,1424,654,679]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1650,1672]" captionTargetBox="[295,1299,919,1623]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[283,1303,911,1628]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 4. Aktedrilus species forming spermatophores (from Swedish Museum of Natural History collection). A. A. mediterraneus (Erséus, 1980), spermatophore in segment XI. B–C. A. arcticus (Erséus, 1978), histological sections of the male duct. D. A. labeosus (Baker &amp; Erséus, 1982), copulatory bursa and glandular organ. E,F. A. mediterraneus, histological sections of the male duct. Abbreviations: a atrium, cb copulatory bursa, go glandular organ, gr glandular ring, ms male sac, o ovary, sf sperm funnel, sph spermatophore, vd vas deferens." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1451102/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
). Placement is either on the dorsal or ventral sides of the body wall, in the clitellar region. The single, dorsal spermatheca is absent in four of these species, but a small spermatheca is present in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Erseus" baseAuthorityYear="1978" box="[1213,1341,727,750]" class="Clitellata" family="Naididae" genus="Aktedrilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="arcticus">
<emphasis box="[1213,1341,727,750]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">A. arcticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Erséus" baseAuthorityYear="1978" class="Clitellata" family="Naididae" genus="Aktedrilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="parvithecatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">A. parvithecatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and can be full of sperm. 
<bibRefCitation box="[624,783,763,787]" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" refId="ref10292" refString="Erseus, C. (1978) Two species of the little-known genus Bacescuella (Hrabe) (Oligochaeta, Tubificidae) from the North Atlantic. Zoologica Scripta, 7, 263 - 269. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1463 - 6409.1978. tb 00609. x" type="journal article">Erséus (1978)</bibRefCitation>
suggested that this has little or no functional relevance; some specimens can bear up to 3 or 4 spermatophores, and the author suggests that the presence of spermathecae can be just a relic of ancestral forms, in which spermatophores had not evolved.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1451102/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" startId="9.[151,250,1650,1672]" targetBox="[295,1299,919,1623]" targetPageId="9">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1650,1794]" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,275,1650,1672]" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">FIGURE 4</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Knollner" authorityYear="1935" box="[294,398,1650,1672]" class="Clitellata" family="Naididae" genus="Aktedrilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[294,398,1650,1672]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">Aktedrilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species forming spermatophores (from Swedish Museum of Natural History collection). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1376,1401,1650,1672]" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">A.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="(Erseus, 1980)" authorityName="Erseus" authorityYear="1980" baseAuthorityName="Erseus" baseAuthorityYear="1980" class="Clitellata" family="Naididae" genus="Aktedrilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="mediterraneus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">A. mediterraneus</emphasis>
(Erséus, 1980)
</taxonomicName>
, spermatophore in segment XI. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[775,830,1680,1702]" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">B–C.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="(Erseus, 1978)" authorityName="Erseus" authorityYear="1978" baseAuthorityName="Erseus" baseAuthorityYear="1978" box="[836,1097,1680,1702]" class="Clitellata" family="Naididae" genus="Aktedrilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="arcticus">
<emphasis box="[836,945,1681,1702]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">A. arcticus</emphasis>
(Erséus, 1978)
</taxonomicName>
, histological sections of the male duct. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[206,231,1711,1733]" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">D.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="(Baker &amp; Erseus, 1982)" authorityName="Baker &amp; Erseus" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Baker &amp; Erseus" baseAuthorityYear="1982" box="[237,599,1711,1733]" class="Clitellata" family="Naididae" genus="Aktedrilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="labeosus">
<emphasis box="[237,353,1711,1733]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">A. labeosus</emphasis>
(Baker &amp; Erséus, 1982)
</taxonomicName>
, copulatory bursa and glandular organ. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[996,1013,1711,1733]" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">E</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1020,1037,1711,1733]" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">F.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Erseus" baseAuthorityYear="1980" box="[1045,1218,1711,1733]" class="Clitellata" family="Naididae" genus="Aktedrilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="mediterraneus">
<emphasis box="[1045,1218,1711,1733]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">A. mediterraneus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, histological sections of the male duct. Abbreviations: 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[486,499,1742,1764]" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">a</emphasis>
atrium, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[584,609,1742,1764]" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">cb</emphasis>
copulatory bursa, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[799,825,1742,1764]" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">go</emphasis>
glandular organ, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1004,1028,1742,1764]" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">gr</emphasis>
glandular ring, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1190,1221,1742,1764]" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">ms</emphasis>
male sac, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1329,1342,1742,1764]" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">o</emphasis>
ovary, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1418,1436,1742,1764]" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">sf</emphasis>
sperm funnel, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[296,334,1772,1794]" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">sph</emphasis>
spermatophore, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[504,531,1772,1794]" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">vd</emphasis>
